story: Munawar Mohammed shared Slidenerd's post to the group: Egyptian Geeks.
name: Slidenerd
description:
Native is dead, Android and IOS app ecosystem is pretty much dying, my journey at coursetro has come to an end, I AM NO LONGER A PART OF COURSETRO and in this moment of transition, I am working out plans that ll take me in a new direction, after all, where's the fun if you don't experiment

If you are a developer, the only 2 things worth learning are Node.js and Python, please dont waste your time and energy doing anything with the rest! and yea please UNINSTALL android studio and Xcode, both are bloatware and pretty much worthless for what the future holds. Where am I getting this from? Talk with the CxO's in your company, they'll tell you the flaws in the app ecosystem and significant increase in expenditure everyday to get customers and manage retention, i had a talk with the top guys running the show in my country

Everyone's future now depends on ONE thing, will google do a Java transition to apps that dont require installation, upgrade and memory on your phones, if the answer  is no, say goodbye to the native app ecoystem in 2 years

End note
I am not asking you to jump out of the window because of an earthquake, i am telling you that is going to be an earthquake headed soon and keep your table ready to hide under it
